# How has the shelling impacted the ability of civilian populations in Kherson to access basic services such as heat, water and electricity?

## Summary
The shelling of Kherson, Ukraine has had a devastating impact on civilian populations, resulting in 4 deaths and 10 wounded, including a 6-year-old girl <font color=#FF3399>[4]</font>. Approximately 80% of the city is now supplied with water, 75% with heat and 90% with electricity <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font>; however, some neighborhoods remain without these services and it is impossible to restore power supply in certain areas due to the constant shelling <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. This has caused rolling blackouts across the country, with 6 million Ukrainians losing power <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font>. The Ukrainian forces have retaliated and hit a concentration of Russian weaponry in Kakhovka on the east bank <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font>. Although efforts are being made to restore these services, the struggle continues in Kherson <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font>.

